{"type":"text","timestamp":1775879841812,"sessionID":"ses_28550e39affe44ngNC3XoJfwct","part":{"id":"prt_d7aafe69c001cHRcJmMz9cBu8S","messageID":"msg_d7aafd176001VdsGdTSVWHhQ9B","sessionID":"ses_28550e39affe44ngNC3XoJfwct","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the complete delta-spec.md with full acceptance scenarios for AR-037 (PCAP analyzer example application):","time":{"start":1775879841810,"end":1775879841810}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879893584,"sessionID":"ses_28550e39affe44ngNC3XoJfwct","part":{"id":"prt_d7aafe814001SWtFbjuPuZFSZB","messageID":"msg_d7aafd176001VdsGdTSVWHhQ9B","sessionID":"ses_28550e39affe44ngNC3XoJfwct","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_3b5c56efb2654fa4a491857c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PCAP analyzer example application in the AgentCube `example` module.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-037\n- **Module**: `example`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Reference Sources**: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`, `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Files to Add\n\n| Path | Description | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI application with SandboxRunner, ReActAgent, Planner, and Reporter | New |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | Dependencies: fastapi, uvicorn, langchain-openai, scapy | New |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | Container image definition | New |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment manifest | New |\n| `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | Usage documentation | New |\n\n---\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| Path | Description | Change Type |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| | | |\n\n---\n\n## Files to Delete\n\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| | |\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-037-001: PCAP Analyzer Module Structure\n\nThe system SHALL provide a complete `example/pcap-analyzer/` module demonstrating AgentCube SDK usage.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-001-A — Module directory exists\n\n- **GIVEN** the workspace root at `example/`\n- **WHEN** the directory is inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap-analyzer/` subdirectory with all required files\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-001-B — Required files present\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n- **WHEN** files are listed\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap_analyzer.py`, `requirements.txt`, `Dockerfile`, `deployment.yaml`, and `README.md`\n\n---\n\n### AR-037-002: PCAP Analyzer FastAPI Application\n\nThe system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that orchestrates PCAP analysis.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-002-A — Application startup with API key\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started with valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable\n- **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n- **THEN** it SHALL initialize LLM client, PLANNER agent, and REPORTER agent\n- **AND** bind to `0.0.0.0:8000`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-002-B — Application startup without API key\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started without a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- **WHEN** the application attempts startup\n- **THEN** startup SHALL fail with an error rather than serve requests\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-002-C — Analyze endpoint accepts file upload\n\n- **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n- **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with a PCAP file upload (`pcap_file` as `UploadFile`)\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-002-D — Analyze endpoint accepts path parameter\n\n- **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n- **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with `pcap_path` form field (alternative to file upload)\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n\n---\n\n### AR-037-003: SandboxRunner Integration\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `SandboxRunner` class that encapsulates AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-003-A — SandboxRunner initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` is constructed with name, namespace, router_url, workload_manager_url, and warmup_sec\n- **WHEN** initialization completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance\n- **AND** be ready to execute commands via `run()`, upload files via `upload_file()`, and can be stopped via `stop()`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-003-B — Context manager support\n\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** the underlying CodeInterpreterClient SHALL be properly stopped\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-003-C — File upload to sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a local PCAP path to analyze\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be uploaded to the remote sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-003-D — Command execution in sandbox\n\n- **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` with an active session\n- **WHEN** `run(command)` is invoked\n- **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and return execution result\n\n---\n\n### AR-037-004: LLM Orchestration (Planner + Reporter)\n\nThe system SHALL implement LLM-based orchestration for PCAP analysis.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-004-A — Planner agent generates analysis script\n\n- **GIVEN** a PCAP file is available in the sandbox\n- **WHEN** the PLANNER agent receives analysis request with context about the file\n- **THEN** it SHALL generate a Python script using scapy to analyze the PCAP\n- **AND** return the script as a string\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-004-B — Reporter agent generates human-readable report\n\n- **GIVEN** analysis results from sandbox execution\n- **WHEN** the REPORTER agent receives the raw results\n- **THEN** it SHALL generate a human-readable analysis report\n- **AND** return the report as a string\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-004-C — ReAct agent coordinates flow\n\n- **GIVEN** a running PCAP analyzer service\n- **WHEN** a client submits a PCAP for analysis\n- **THEN** the ReAct agent SHALL orchestrate: upload file → generate script → execute → generate report\n\n---\n\n### AR-037-005: PCAP Analyzer Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL read configuration from environment variables with appropriate defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-005-A — Default configuration values\n\n- **GIVEN** the service starts with only `OPENAI_API_KEY` set\n- **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n- **THEN** it SHALL use:\n  - `OPENAI_API_BASE`: default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`\n  - `OPENAI_MODEL`: default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`\n  - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`: default `my-interpreter`\n  - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`: default `default`\n  - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`: default `5`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-005-B — Environment variable overrides\n\n- **GIVEN** environment variables `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` are set\n- **WHEN** the service starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided values instead of defaults\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-005-C — Required environment variables\n\n- **GIVEN** the service starts without `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `ROUTER_URL`, or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n- **WHEN** the application attempts to start\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise a configuration error indicating the missing required variables\n\n---\n\n### AR-037-006: PCAP Analyzer Dependencies\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `requirements.txt` with pinned dependency versions.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-006-A — Dependency file content\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n- **THEN** it SHALL include at minimum: `fastapi>=0.120.0`, `uvicorn`, `langchain-openai`, `scapy`, `agentcube-sdk`\n- **AND** all versions SHALL be pinned or have compatible version specifiers\n\n---\n\n### AR-037-007: PCAP Analyzer Container Image\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Dockerfile for building the analyzer container.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-007-A — Dockerfile base and entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` is built\n- **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n- **THEN** it SHALL use a Python base image, set appropriate `PYTHONPATH`, expose port `8000`, and run the FastAPI application\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-007-B — SDK vendoring\n\n- **GIVEN** the Dockerfile build context includes the agentcube SDK\n- **WHEN** the image is built\n- **THEN** it SHALL include the SDK in the image for the application to import\n\n---\n\n### AR-037-008: PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Kubernetes deployment manifest.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-008-A — Deployment manifest structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n- **WHEN** applied to a cluster\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a Deployment with appropriate container image, port, and resource configuration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-008-B — Environment variable wiring\n\n- **GIVEN** the deployment is applied\n- **WHEN** the pod starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL have required environment variables configured:\n  - `OPENAI_API_KEY` (from secret)\n  - `OPENAI_API_BASE`\n  - `OPENAI_MODEL`\n  - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n  - `ROUTER_URL`\n  - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`\n  - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`\n  - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n\n---\n\n### AR-037-009: SDK Integration\n\nThe system SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK for code interpreter operations.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-009-A — SDK import\n\n- **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` runs analysis\n- **WHEN** it needs to execute code in a sandbox\n- **THEN** it SHALL import `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube.code_interpreter`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-009-B — Context manager usage\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in `SandboxRunner`\n- **WHEN** the runner enters context manager\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a session via ControlPlaneClient and initialize data plane\n- **AND** when exiting context, it SHALL properly stop and delete the session\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-009-C — SDK exception handling\n\n- **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (from `agentcube.exceptions`) with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` attributes\n\n---\n\n### AR-037-010: PCAP Analysis Workflow\n\nThe system SHALL execute a complete PCAP analysis workflow.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-010-A — Complete analysis flow\n\n- **GIVEN** a running PCAP analyzer service with all required configuration\n- **WHEN** a client uploads a valid PCAP file to `/analyze`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Upload the PCAP file to the sandbox\n  2. Generate analysis Python script via PLANNER\n  3. Execute the script in the sandbox\n  4. Collect execution results\n  5. Generate human-readable report via REPORTER\n  6. Return response with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-010-B — Invalid PCAP file handling\n\n- **GIVEN** a client uploads a file that is not a valid PCAP\n- **WHEN** the analysis is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating the file is not a valid PCAP\n\n#### Scenario: AR-037-010-C — Large file handling\n\n- **GIVEN** a client uploads a PCAP file exceeding reasonable size limits\n- **WHEN** the upload is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating file size limit exceeded\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory contains all required files\n- [ ] AC002: FastAPI application starts successfully with valid `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- [ ] AC003: FastAPI application fails to start without `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n- [ ] AC004: `/analyze` endpoint accepts file upload and returns AnalyzeResponse\n- [ ] AC005: `/analyze` endpoint accepts path parameter as alternative\n- [ ] AC006: SandboxRunner provides upload_file, run, and stop methods\n- [ ] AC007: SandboxRunner supports context manager protocol\n- [ ] AC008: PLANNER agent generates Python script using scapy\n- [ ] AC009: REPORTER agent generates human-readable report\n- [ ] AC010: ReAct agent orchestrates the complete analysis flow\n- [ ] AC011: Configuration uses defaults when env vars are not set\n- [ ] AC012: Required environment variables are validated at startup\n- [ ] AC013: requirements.txt contains all required dependencies\n- [ ] AC014: Dockerfile builds successfully and runs the application\n- [ ] AC015: Kubernetes deployment manifest is valid and deployable\n- [ ] AC016: SDK exceptions are properly handled\n- [ ] AC017: Invalid PCAP file returns appropriate error\n- [ ] AC018: README.md contains usage instructions\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Changes\n\n| Key | Old Value | New Value | Description |\n|-----|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n| | | | |\n\n---\n\n## Database Schema Changes\n\n| Table | Change | SQL |\n|-------|--------|-----|\n| | | |\n\n---\n\n## API Changes\n\n### New APIs\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| POST | `/analyze` | Analyze PCAP file with LLM orchestration |\n\n### Modified APIs\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| | | |\n\n### Deprecated APIs\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| | | |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| Main Application | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI application entry point |\n| SandboxRunner | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient wrapper |\n| Planner Agent | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | LLM agent for generating analysis scripts |\n| Reporter Agent | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | LLM agent for generating reports |\n| Dependencies | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | Python package dependencies |\n| Container | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | Container image definition |\n| Deployment | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment manifest |\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Required | Description |\n|----------|---------|----------|-------------|\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | - | Yes | OpenAI-compatible API key |\n| `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` | No | API endpoint |\n| `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` | No | Model name |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | - | Yes | AgentCube Workload Manager URL |\n| `ROUTER_URL` | - | Yes | AgentCube Router URL |\n| `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | `my-interpreter` | No | Code interpreter name |\n| `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | `default` | No | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | `5` | No | Sandbox warmup duration |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Proposal: `changes/AR-037/proposal.md`\n- SDK design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- SDK spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- Reference source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879893553,"end":1775879893580}}}}
